The paper deals with the privacy threat of information leakage from mobile and wearable devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of game theory to model the interaction between mobile applications and the on-board defense mechanism suggests a focus on decision-making and strategic behavior, which could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the dynamic nature of sensor usage and the need for access control mechanisms, which could be related to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
